Axial tilt ?° Albedo 0.04 (assumed) Surface temp. {| cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" border="0" min mean max ~65 K (estimate) Trinculo is a retrograde non-spherical moon of Uranus. It was found by Holman, et al. on 2001-08-13, and given the designation S/2001 U 1.IAU Circular IAUC 7980: S/2001 U 1, September 30, 2002 Gladman, B. J.; Kavelaars, J. J.; Holman, M. A.; The Discovery of Uranus XIX, XX, and XXI, Icarus, 147 (2000), pp. 320–324 Confirmed as Uranus XXI, it was named after the drunken jester Trinculo in William Shakespeare's play The Tempest. ==Related pages== * List of Uranus' moons == References == *Ephemeris IAU-NSES *Mean orbital parameters NASA JPL == Other websites == * David C.
